Sometimes you just gotta look up and you might find a gem. I was walking my pup head-down focused in December 2021 when he jumped at a passerby and her dog. Fast forward a year later and we’ve been dating ever since.

My preference is to use social media for business and to inspire. Not a huge fan of sharing lots of personal stuff publicly and don’t feel the need to prove how much I love my girlfriend by posting on social media. I don’t like how so many people just post highlights. We all go through shit. We all have tough moments. We all cry and we hopefully all laugh. We all fail and we all persevere. We all lose and we all win.

To avoid solely posting highlights and to not over share or frankly give it too much energy… I’d be remiss to not give a little context to these travels. Long story as short as possible… I unfortunately experienced a “life isn’t always fair” moment. My neighbor was mentally unstable (understatement) and a very good fighter. To put it simply - police were involved with him several times. Borderline traumatizing experience. Unprovoked (actually) he messed with me and others and as my apartment was right next to his I got the worst of it. The landlord was trying to evict him and asked him to leave but it wasn’t a quick process.

I decided to ask to get out of my lease, put all my stuff in storage and travel the country in my girlfriend’s van while mainly sleeping in Airbnb’s and seeing friends and fam along the way for about 6 months. 

We did Vegas, LA, Phoenix, Grand Canyon, Sedona, Portland, Washington, NYC, Cape Cod, Boise, Truckee and more.

It was a tough decision because I loved my place which was basically on the beach in Laguna Beach. It was my sanctuary (until it wasn’t), which I worked very hard for. 

I told myself we’d upgrade in the next spot despite feeling like that would be hard to do. It was achieved. Def not saying that to boast but some lessons I can pass on to anyone who may need a reminder… life is full of shit. Turn that shit into lemonade. Or is it turn lemons into lemonade? Keep calm, carry on? 

PS - everyone deserves a partner who makes them better. Thankful to have that and she knows how much I ADORE her.

My journey like yours has been full of ups and downs. This video focuses more on the ups and the fact that I’m now offering “coaching” services. That title is cheesy. “Coaching”.  A lot of my learnings have come from the downs. The struggles. The uncertainties. The loneliness. The moments of pain. The moments of frustration. The times when my back has been against the wall and it felt like I was stuck in between a rock and a rock (not even just a hard place).   I’ve walked the walk for a long time. 

Strong insights have emerged from certain wins.  There’s a lot I don’t know, but a lot I do know. My last name is Weissenstein, not Einstein.
 When it comes to figuring out how to live a better balanced life, successfully freelancing, building a remote work lifestyle, closing deals, solving problems, finding areas to achieve more happiness, building your brand, driving leads, converting sales, gaining motivation/inspiration, goal setting and more… I may be able to help.
 Further, only accepting $ from people who see the value. No risk.  Watch the video 🤷🏼‍♂️  Moving forward, I’m going to try to not be salesy, but starting next week for at least a year straight I’ll be posting weekly posts. The goal is content that is creative and brings some form of value through insights, motivation, laughs or something in between. I’ll do my best to create content that achieves those forms of value and if there’s anything that you think could be specifically helpful to people on their journey in terms of content from me, let me know. Or if you’re seeking help on your journey, shoot me a DM and let’s chat. 
 Cheers 👊🏼

For the first post in a series this year which I hope will add some sort of value to you, let’s focus on how we can’t become successful by ourselves. In other words, “You can’t reach the throne alone.”

We can achieve a lot without help. Kind of.  Can’t get to our real dreams without some help along the way doe. To achieve anything of significance, there’s usually someone helping in some way whether it be a coach or trainer or team member or investor or friend or family member or partner helping with advice or opening a door or money or connecting to someone who helps unlock a door for you or, you get it. 

Don’t be afraid to network or ask for help. We’re all in this life thing together and are able to help each other. 

PS - some of what I post are reminders to myself which I think may help others too. 🤷🏼‍♂️

It’s so easy to lay back/not work as hard when we achieve any success. I’ve unfortunately done this multiple times in my career. I’ve achieved something and then didn’t stay as focused or work as hard.

Learn from my mistakes. “Don’t forsake it once you make it.” 

Stay hungry. Stay focused. Push even harder when you achieve something. Don’t let up. Get and keep momentum. 🚀

We all wish we could reach our dreams on day one. It would be nice to reach our dreams without needing to struggle and wait and feel the moments of uncertainty.

I’ll never forget a conversation I had with a friend who I knew in high school who ended up making it to the NBA. The conversation I had with him was during his first season in the NBA. He wasn’t a close friend, but we both shared a close friend in common. He was back in town and this was the only time we ever hungout just him and I. He spoke about how he missed the journey. I remember thinking… man easy for you to say, you now have made it to your dreams. That stuck with me doe. I try to remind myself whenever I’m frustrated with not being where I want to be yet that there’s so much beauty in the journey. 

If you work hard, stay persistent and consistent while evolving, you will be able to realize a beautiful dream of yours. 

“Your dream is just a matter of time. Stay on your grind.”

Figure out the issue(s) and take action instead of just feeling shitty and bad for ourselves. Nobody wants to feel shitty and nobody wants to be around people who have bad energy. Figure out why and take action. 

“Ask why. Don’t sigh.”

The premise… a jury duty documentary although there’s more to it. Everyone’s an actor except one person (Ronald). He doesn’t know everyone else is an actor till the very end. Was a bit skeptical but by the last episode I can say without a doubt he really didn’t know the entire time. Good reminder that there are still good people out there. May or may not have shed a few tears at the end. There’s humor and inspiration to be found in this experience and it’s worth having to watch some ads even though I hate ads. That’s how good this show or “experience” is. All the characters, even those not in this pic and those behind the scenes pulled off a masterpiece. 

Find some time after (or during) work for this and you won’t be disappointed. 🍿 @amazonfreevee

These guys. Probably about 9 months ago or so I was served a random video on YouTube. It was a Football team (Jackson State) showing some behind the scenes content. I quickly went from “what is this?” to super intrigued. Timing was funny - it happened to be right before Coach Prime decided to leave for his next opportunity, coaching at the University of Colorado. I’d definitely heard of Deion Sanders and knew vaguely he was a superb athlete but as someone who didn’t follow Football much (Baseball was my sport), I didn’t know that much and sure didn’t know about his transition to Coach Prime and all the glorious things he’s done and achieved in the past years. 

There are 3 main channels who have followed the journey behind the scenes… Well Off Media, Thee Pregame Show, Reach The People Media. 

As someone who has gone through a range of adversity (haven’t we all) and as someone who has done a lot of grinding, had a lot of ups and downs, and has been incredibly persistent chasing my dreams… I can relate to this journey. Ever since I found out about these channels I’ve watched religiously while I work remotely on my computer, having their footage playing multiple times throughout the day each day. It’s been one more source of motivation for me. Lots of ways to relate Football and the building of programs to entrepreneurship/business. There are so many backstories from people coming and going and struggles along the way (just like life) and these guys have a good sense of humor. 

So much more to say but I’ll end with these 3 points for now…
1) If you’ve ever enjoyed Mighty Ducks or Remember the Titans as I have, you may want to start checking out these channels. 

2) The program they’ve completely revamped is a program that before them (last year) went 1 and 11 (that’s 1 win, 11 losses). While analysts seem to say if they win 5 this year it will be a major turnaround, I have a strong feeling they’re going to do much better than that and truly shock the world. 

3) If you’re a man who could use another good male figure to look up to even if not necessarily in your physical life, look no further than Coach Prime. 

“WE COMING”
Entrepreneur/dreamer/dude on this life journey.
